Write a method to replace all spaces in a string with %20. 
The string is given in a characters array, you can assume it has enough space 
for replacement and you are given the true length of the string.

Example
Given "Mr John Smith", length = 13.

The string after replacement should be "Mr%20John%20Smith".

Note
If you are using Java or Pythonï¼Œplease use characters array instead of string.

Challenge
Do it in-place.
===============
public class Solution {
    /**
     * @param string: An array of Char
     * @param length: The true length of the string
     * @return: The true length of new string
     */
    public int replaceBlank(char[] string, int length) {
        if (string == null) return 0;
        int space = 0;
        for (char str: string) {
            if (str == ' ') {
                space++;
            }
        }
        
        int newLen = length + 2*space -1;
        for (int i=length-1; i>=0; i--) {
            if (string[i] != ' ') {
                string[newLen] = string[i];
                newLen--;
            } else {
                string[newLen--] = '0';
                string[newLen--] = '2';
                string[newLen--] = '%';
            }
        }
        
        return length+2*space;
    }
}
